subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 27
) general characters: genitalia very small; lateral margins of parameres almost parallel; paramere tips rounded and curving toward midline, but not contacting one another, tips smaller than distal part of aedeagus, very lightly sclerotized; aedeagus wide, much wider that narrowest part of parameres; basal piece markedly tapering from distal to proximal, widened at orifice, in lateral view, with ventral ½ very weakly sclerotized, dorsal ½ strongly sclerotized, rim of orifice sclerotized, strongly produced apicoventrally in point, toward dorsad.
